<br>
1. Ion exchaust velocity ve in meters per second  = 2 * (the sqaure root of the ion charge q /m  the ions mass in kilograms *  (va) the acclerating voltage of the total cumalative electric fields in which the ion is accelerated .<br>
<br>
2. Thrust in pounds  = (ve) the exchaust velocity in feet<br>
 per second * by the mass of the ion beam expelled per second in pounds.<br>
For example an exchaust velocity of 900 kilometers per second is    900,000 meters per second which is <br>
2,700,000 feet per second.<br>
 <br>
1000 grams = 1 kilogram.<br>
<br>
454.54 grams = 1 pound <br>
<br>
for 1 gram of mass Thrust in pounds is 2, 700,000 /454.54<br>
which  is 5940 pounds. In kilograms this  is 2700 kilograms<br>
<br>
<br>
Acceleration in meters per second  = the thrust in kilograms/<br>
the mass in kilograms of the object.<br>
<br>
2700/2,700,000 kilograms yields an acceleration of<br>
.001 meters per socond.<br>
Delta V = acceleration * time T<br>
<br>
 There are 31,536,000 seconds in a year.<br>
31563000/1000 is = 31,563 meters per second<br>
This is  31563 * 3 =94,689 feet per second /<br>
5280. = 17.93 miles a second which is 67,261 miles an hour <br>
 1 mile a second = 3751.33 miles per hour<br>
<br>
The rocket eqaution <br>
V = ve * ln mi/mf<br>
